<paragraph blockId="4.[810,1422,1794,2091]" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,971,1899,1923]" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Identification.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ryvarden, L" box="[1132,1316,1900,1924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="327" refId="ref6163" refString="Ryvarden, L (2004) Neotropical Polypores, part 1: introduction, Hymenochaetaceae and Ganodermataceae. Synopsis fungorum, volume 9. Fungiflora, Oslo, Norway, 227 pp." type="book" year="2004">Ryvarden (2004)</bibRefCitation>
this species has the following characters: basidiome perennial, resupinate (
<figureCitation box="[935,1015,1967,1991]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-35@5.[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia langloisii. B. F. maxonii. C. F. murrillii. D. F. neotropica." pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); hymenophore with circular to angular pores, 4–7 per mm (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1155,2000,2024]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-35@5.[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia langloisii. B. F. maxonii. C. F. murrillii. D. F. neotropica." pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); context homogeneous, thin, yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[1067,1150,2033,2058]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-35@5.[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia langloisii. B. F. maxonii. C. F. murrillii. D. F. neotropica." pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); hyphal system dimitic, with generative hyphae hyaline, thin-walled, septate
</paragraph>
