<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="330" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[168,779,160,424]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,317,266,290]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is widely distributed throughout the Americas (
<bibRefCitation author="Ryvarden, L" box="[372,544,300,324]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" refId="ref6163" refString="Ryvarden, L (2004) Neotropical Polypores, part 1: introduction, Hymenochaetaceae and Ganodermataceae. Synopsis fungorum, volume 9. Fungiflora, Oslo, Norway, 227 pp." type="book" year="2004">Ryvarden 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Decock C &amp; Figueroa SH &amp; Robledo G &amp; Castillo G" box="[556,766,300,324]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" pagination="733 - 752" refId="ref5299" refString="Decock C, Figueroa SH, Robledo G, Castillo G (2007) Fomitiporia punctata (Basidiomycota, Hymenochaetales) and its presumed taxonomic synonyms in America: taxonomy and phylogeny of some species from tropical / subtropical areas. Mycologia 99 (5): 733 - 752. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 15572536.2007.11832537" type="journal article" year="2007">Decock et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), including in some states of southern 
<collectingCountry box="[588,655,333,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ryvarden L &amp; Meijer AAR" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" pagination="34 - 69" refId="ref6128" refString="Ryvarden L, Meijer AAR (2002) Studies in Neotropical polypores 14. New species from the state of Parana, Brazil. Synopsis Fungorum 15 (1): 34 - 69." type="journal article" year="2002">Ryvarden and Meijer 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Our record is the first from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[168,238,400,424]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
